<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="28.[264,1323,427,1854]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,426,1748,1774]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Remarks</emphasis>
: This species, the third known, can be distinguished from both 
<taxonomicName authority="Koehler" authorityName="Koehler" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiolepididae" genus="Ophiomidas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="alatum">
<emphasis box="[1202,1323,1748,1773]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">O. alatum</emphasis>
Koehler
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Koehler" authorityName="Koehler" box="[418,667,1788,1814]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiolepididae" genus="Ophiomidas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="reductum">
<emphasis box="[418,564,1788,1813]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">O. reductum</emphasis>
Koehler
</taxonomicName>
in having small granules at the margin and ventrally, a four­sided oral shield and in having 
<number box="[688,703,1828,1854]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="3.0">3</number>
armspines.
</paragraph>
